Wednesday Wisdom: Graphic designers Miraphora Mina and Eduardo Lima, who created the book covers seen throughout Harry Potter, created multiple copies in various sizes for the films. "When the book needed to be read close up on-camera, we'd do a version that would be 20 to 50% bigger," Lima explains. "This was especially important when the handwriting needed to be visible, as with the Advanced Potion-Making book."

status_message:
Calling all Harry Potter fans around the world!
Whether you've grown up with Harry, Ron and Hermione or you're new to Hogwarts, it's time to come together and celebrate! 

This January, fans are congregating at Universal Orlando Resort for A Celebration of Harry Potter, but don't worry, you don't have to be in Orlando to celebrate. We're asking fans to join in the celebration from home as we bring you the best bits, and with some exciting activity just for you and friends online, through this event page. 

So invite your friends over for the weekend, get your Harry Potter creative hats on, and get ready for:
- A worldwide watch along on Sunday
- Special access to some of the Harry Potter cast
- Live Q&A moments and videos 
- And much more!
 
Itâ€™s the time of year to celebrate all things Harry Potter! So, how will you be celebrating?

Friday 27 - Sunday 29
